tip.text: Love the food here. Service is okay.
Food is amazing but very poor service. Need to keep asking for spoon and fork, and the bill and takeout took a while.

It's overrated and pricey. At Php 99 per cup you get 2 toppings on vanilla ice cream surrounded by cotton candy. I got kitkat (only one piece broken in half) and caramel popcorn (less than a handful).
Chicken and fries are good but they are small in portion.
Matcha bingsu is so-so. The beans and nuts are overpowering the green tea. Waffles aren't that good. The hotdogs are tasty but are overpriced as they look similar to Family Mart's except w/ toppings.

tip.text: Bbq and garlic wings are soooo good. The leftmost one in the photo is the buffalo wings which is the least of my favorite but still very, very good.
Jack Daniel's burger is really good. Seafood pasta is yummy but portion is too small.
Fun experience of having food ordered from a screen and delivered via (train) conveyor belt. Unagi Don and Black Pepper Chicken rice are so good.
Salted Egg flavored Shrimps are the best! Buffalo chicken wings in photo are so good but it can be a bit too spicy.

formattedAddress: Ground Flr, Grand Hampton (at 2nd Ave & 31st St)

tip.text: Yummy yummy Mozarella Sticks. The booths are great for large groups. On Sunday nights they aren't crowded at all.
Absolutely loved the Bacon Quesadilla! Bbq stick and the Sisig Tacos are good also
Eggs Benedict Pancakes are so good!
Hibachi Pork Tapa Lazy Sushi is yummy. I like the novelty of sushi burritos but are too messy to eat because your teeth wont be able to tear the nori wrap. Mojos were undercooked & lacked breading.
The "new" Osaka Teriyaki Zinger is really just the regular Zinger with chopped up veggies. Serving of Teriyaki sauce is too little to matter.

formattedAddress: Ground Flr, Teleperformance Ayala (at Ayala Ave. & Amorsolo St.)

tip.text: Pretty chill place to drink.
The onion rings is especially good. It's cooked crunchy but is on the greasy side. The burger reminds me of In-n-out. You can swap out the buns for lettuce wrap if you add P20.
Deja Vu is soooo good! It's warm mango crepe with vanilla ice cream. We also had the chance to acquaint with the owner who is very nice and humble.

formattedAddress: Ground Flr, Greenbelt 3 (btwn Greenbelt Dr. & Makati Ave.)

tip.text: Booked using BookyApp. Food is so good especially the Karaage appetizers.
This place is an underrated gem. Love the burgers! It's around the same price as Brothers Burgers except this one is worth the price. Definitely coming back.
Ox tongue and Squid Ink paella is soooo good. But the price is quite expensive considering the serving.
Paitan Ramen is one of the best white broth ramen I've ever tried. Big serving of pork and the soup is just addicting. I'd finish it all if I didnt get full from the large portion.

formattedAddress: 2nd Flr, Glorietta 5 (at Ayala Ave & East Dr)

tip.text: Mabo Tofu Tsukemen is good and the serving is big. I had half for takeout.

Good only for a first try. Kids will enjoy it. The queue is too long.

Very authentic! Place is cozy bordering on lonely because of the lights. But will definitely come back.
Nice concept. Love the drinks. Cheesy fries are delicious.
Must order the chili crab and salted egg prawns.
Love their duck! It's so tender. Chicken lollipop and the spareribs are great to go with it.
Absolutely love the ambience and the food. Adore the cashless system of ordering. That rosti with sour cream is so simple yet to die for. The sandwich wrap and the fried silverfish are must try!
Their Chicken Chop rice is the best. Affordable too!

Yummy calamares. Love their dip!

Calamares Pritos for appetizer!
